i$ is quenched by the strong intensities $B$, then for the annulus this\ntakes place only when the inner Robin distance $\\Lambda_{in}$ is real;\notherwise, it almost quadratically depends on $B$ with the corresponding\nenhancement of the reactive scattering. Closely related problem of the hole in\nthe otherwise uniform medium is also addressed for real and complex\nextrapolation lengths with the emphasis on the comparative analysis with its\ndot counterpart.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2011 22:20:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-03-14"}
